{"name":"Antonio Ciliegia - Gullible Alchemist","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"adversary","isMainNPC":true,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am an old alchemist who has never discovered anything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck is never on my side."],"agenda":["Obtaining the secret of eternal life thanks to alchemy"],"gifts":[{"name":"Unlucky Alchemist","description":"Antonio can rely on a series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides in his tunic. When using a vial he rolls 1 die. On a 5 or 6 something goes wrong and Antonio suffers 1 Wound due to his proverbial bad luck. 1. Fire: The target and the surrounding area catch fire. All targets involved suffer 1 Wound. If the fire is not extinguished, burning targets suffer 1 Wound per action. 2. Thunder: The target is knocked over thirty feet away and ends up on the ground. If they hit something they will suffer 1 Wound. 3. Glue: an adhesive compound that quickly solidifies in the air. The target will be paralyzed until the compound is removed. The Glue can take 2 Wounds."}],"background":"Known as Mastro 'Cherry' Ciliegia because of his squat and red nose. An old alchemist who partnered with Geppetto to discover the secret of eternal life. Works on a magic oak tree and has been kidnapping people in Sinalunga to flay them for their skin. Now hiding in Villa Cilesterino with Azzurra's spirit.","notes":"His apprentice Nino is currently tied up in the Secret Laboratory. Antonio's workshop was the original scene of the experiments before they fled to Villa Cilesterino.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","inspiration":"Pinocchio (Carlo Collodi)","role":"Antagonist - Alchemist"},"_id":"5f62ddef22d85c4d"}
{"name":"Carlo - The Living Puppet","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"adversary","isMainNPC":true,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The lies I tell become reality for a short time."],"agenda":["Living a carefree life without responsibility","I don't want to abandon Sinalunga and my new friend Lucino, but I'm always afraid that Geppetto and Antonio will catch me"],"gifts":[{"name":"Lies","description":"Carlo can bring the lies he tells to life by creating a Descriptor that allows him to perform incredible feats. All lies must be centered on him. For example: I can walk through walls or I am invisible to the human eye. The effects of the lies' power are literal. For this reason, Carlo would not be able to go through a closed door and he would be seen by animals. The effect of Lies lasts for 1 Scene or until a new lie is told."}],"background":"A wooden puppet animated by fairy magic from an enchanted oak tree. By nature, Carlo cannot speak even a single word of truth. His lies convinced Geppetto and Antonio that they needed to flay people alive for their experiments. Horrified by what he caused, Carlo escaped to Sinalunga where he disguises himself as a real child every morning using his powers. Attends school and has befriended Lucino. Wears old elegant shoes given to him by Geppetto. Currently hiding at Villa Balocchi, paying the innkeeper with stones temporarily transformed into gold coins.","notes":"Carlo unwittingly created the horror in Sinalunga but is not evil - he's terrified of being caught by Geppetto and Antonio. Can be redeemed if Hunters gain his trust. Azzurra's spirit wants to use his fairy magic to return to life.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","inspiration":"Pinocchio (Carlo Collodi)","role":"Morally Ambiguous - Living Puppet"},"_id":"112b612073816e0c"}
{"name":"Geppetto - Gullible Alchemist","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"adversary","isMainNPC":true,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a poor man who has always been looking for a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy from master Antonio."],"agenda":["Pretend to be Carlo's father and find him","Obtain the secret of eternal life, thanks to alchemy"],"gifts":[{"name":"Improvised Alchemist","description":"Geppetto can rely on a series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides under a tacky yellow wig. When he throws a vial, roll a die: 1-2 Explosive: The liquid explodes on contact with the air, causing 1 Wound to everyone within thirty feet. Thick black smoke will engulf the whole area; 3-4 Stench: A nauseating odor fills the air giving 1 Penalty to all actions within the area for the rest of the Scene; 5-6 Air Bomb: All subjects in an area of thirty feet are knocked back and fall to the ground. If they hit an obstacle they can suffer 1 Wound. Geppetto is immune to the effects of his alchemical concoctions."}],"background":"One of two alchemists who kidnapped people in Sinalunga to experiment on them. Geppetto believes Carlo is the key to eternal life and is desperately searching for the living puppet. Wears a tacky yellow wig that hides his alchemical vials.","notes":"Appears at the Gambero Rosso Inn playing the role of a worried father looking for his 'son' Carlo. Will describe Carlo's old elegant shoes as a clue.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","inspiration":"Pinocchio (Carlo Collodi)","role":"Antagonist - Alchemist"},"_id":"7c7e019ee852c0f1"}